<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8"/>
    <title>Top of the Poops</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Analysing sewage dumps by water companies in the UK">

    {{> chunks/favicons }}
    {{> chunks/meta-styles }}
    {{> chunks/meta-scripts }}

    <!-- Bootstrap Icons -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap-icons@1.11.1/font/bootstrap-icons.css">

    <!-- Custom Styles -->
    <style>
        .hover-shadow:hover {
            box-shadow: 0 .5rem 1rem rgba(0,0,0,.15)!important;
        }
        .transition {
            transition: all 0.3s ease;
        }
        .sewage-map {
            min-height: 400px;
        }
        /* Equal height columns for the sewage everywhere section */
        .sewage-columns-equal-height {
            display: flex;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
        }
        .sewage-columns-equal-height > [class*='col-'] {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
        }
        .sewage-columns-equal-height:after,
        .sewage-columns-equal-height:before {
            display: flex;
        }
    </style>

    {{> components/meta-opengraph
            title="Homepage"
            twitterImageUri=share.twitterImageUri
    }}

    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
</head>
<body>
{{> chunks/navbar }}

{{#> components/jumbotron }}
    <div class="text-center py-4">
        <h1 class="display-3 fw-bold mb-4">Tracking Sewage Pollution</h1>
        <p class="lead fs-3 mb-4">
            At least <em class="text-danger fw-bold">{{numberFormat totalCount}}</em> sewage spills
            into waterways in {{year}}, lasting
            <span class="badge bg-danger fs-4">{{numberFormat totalDuration.hours}} hours</span>
            <br/>That's <em class="text-danger fw-bold">{{numberFormat totalDuration.years}} years!</em>
        </p>
        <a href="/support" class="btn btn-danger btn-lg px-4 py-2">Support Our Work</a>
    </div>
{{/components/jumbotron}}


<div class="container-fluid py-5">
    <div class="row justify-content-md-center g-4 sewage-columns-equal-height">
        <div class="col-md-5">
            <div class="position-relative">
                <img alt="A stylised map of England and Wales showing CSO locations" class="img-fluid rounded " src="/assets/images/top-of-the-poops-cso-2023-web-fs8.png"/>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4 align-top">
            <div class="card border-0">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h2 class="card-title fw-bold text-danger mb-3">A Petri Dish for E.Coli</h2>

                    <p class="card-text">Here are all the CSOs in England & Wales that 'overflowed' in {{ year }} - Scotland data is coming soon! - dumping raw or
                        minimally treated sewage into fragile chalk streams, rivers, onto beaches and into shellfish
                        areas.</p>
                    <p class="card-text">Each colour represents a different Water Company, the size of each dot relates to how long each
                        overflow was polluting - where the monitoring is disabled we show a medium-sized dot.</p>
                    <p class="card-text"><small class="text-muted">The figures, supplied by the water companies themselves, understate the problem, as the data is
                        poorly collected by the Water Companies, with monitoring defective or in many cases completely absent.</small></p>

                    <div class="d-flex gap-2 mb-4">
                        {{> components/share-facebook share}}
                        {{> components/share-twitter share}}
                    </div>

                    <div class="alert alert-warning p-3 mb-3">
                        <div class="d-flex align-items-center mb-2">
                            <i class="bi bi-heart-fill text-danger me-2 fs-4"></i>
                            <h5 class="mb-0">We need your support!</h5>
                        </div>
                        <p class="mb-2">We managed to raise Â£150 in 2024. That's not enough to keep the site running. Please consider a one-off or small recurring donation.</p>
                        <a href="/support" class="btn btn-danger">
                            <i class="bi bi-heart me-1"></i> Donate Now
                        </a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row justify-content-md-center my-4 g-4 sewage-columns-equal-height">
        <div class="col-md-4 offset-md-2">
            <div class="card border-0">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h2 class="card-title fw-bold text-primary mb-3">Sewage Everywhere</h2>

                    <p class="card-text">There is sewage overflowing into rivers in almost every constituency
                        across England and Wales. A very few miss out, simply because they don't
                        have any Combined Sewage Overflows.</p>

                    <div class="alert alert-info p-3 mb-3">
                        <p class="mb-0"><strong>What are CSOs?</strong> CSOs mix toilet sewage with rainwater and
                        then discharge it into rivers, creating a horrible environment for fish and other creatures - it
                        poisons them, and the rivers die.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="card bg-light mb-4">
                        <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
                            <h5 class="mb-0">Top of The Poops - Constituencies</h5>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-body p-0">
                            <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
                                {{#each constituencyRankings}}
                                    <li class="list-group-item d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center">
                                        <div>
                                            <span class="badge bg-primary rounded-pill me-2">{{this.rank}}</span>
                                            <a href="{{this.constituency.uri}}" class="text-decoration-none">{{this.constituency.name}}</a>
                                        </div>
                                        <span class="badge bg-danger rounded-pill">{{numberFormat this.duration.hours}} hours</span>
                                    </li>
                                {{/each}}
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <a href="/constituencies" class="btn btn-primary d-block">
                        <i class="bi bi-list-ol me-1"></i> See All Constituency Rankings
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="card border-0">
                <div class="card-body align-top">
                    <div id="map-constituency" class="sewage-map rounded"></div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row justify-content-md-center align-items-center my-5 g-4 sewage-columns-equal-height">
        <div class="col-md-5 offset-md-1">
            <div class="card border-0">
                <div class="card-body p-0">
                    <div id="map-beaches" class="sewage-map rounded"></div>
                </div>
                <div class="card-footer bg-info text-white py-2">
                    <small><i class="bi bi-info-circle me-1"></i> Interactive map of beach sewage spills</small>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="card border-0">
                <div class="card-body p-4">
                    <h2 class="card-title fw-bold text-info mb-3">Swimming in Sewage</h2>

                    <p class="card-text">Most, if not actually all, of the beaches and designated coastal bathing locations around England
                        and Wales are regular recipients of a good layer of sewage.</p>

                    <div class="alert alert-warning mb-3">
                        <div class="d-flex">
                            <div class="me-2">
                                <i class="bi bi-exclamation-triangle-fill fs-4 text-warning"></i>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <h5 class="alert-heading">Accuracy Warning</h5>
                                <p class="mb-0">We use data from the water companies, but we are seeing many anomalies that make us believe that
                                bathing location information is quite poor. The situation is likely <b>far worse</b> than reported here.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <p class="card-text">Water companies have a duty to report on the summer bathing season separately, and this made grim
                        reading in 2022.
                        For more details check out <a href="https://www.sas.org.uk/waterquality2022/" class="text-info">Surfers Against Sewage
                            Water Quality Report 2022</a></p>

                    <div class="card bg-light mb-4">
                        <div class="card-header bg-info text-white">
                            <h5 class="mb-0">Top of The Poops - Beaches</h5>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-body p-0">
                            <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
                                {{#each beachRankings}}
                                    <li class="list-group-item d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center">
                                        <div>
                                            <span class="badge bg-info rounded-pill me-2">{{this.rank}}</span>
                                            <small class="text-muted me-1">{{this.company.name}} -</small>
                                            <a href="{{this.beach.uri}}" class="text-decoration-none">{{this.beach.name}}</a>
                                        </div>
                                        <span class="badge bg-danger rounded-pill">{{numberFormat this.duration.hours}} hours</span>
                                    </li>
                                {{/each}}
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <a href="/beaches" class="btn btn-info text-white d-block">
                        <i class="bi bi-water me-1"></i> See All Beach Rankings
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>


    <div class="row justify-content-md-center align-items-center my-5 g-4">
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="card border-0  h-100">
                <div class="card-body p-4">
                    <h2 class="card-title fw-bold text-success mb-3">Rivers & Streams</h2>

                    <p class="card-text">Of the 4700 rivers in England, few escape from sewage dumping.</p>

                    <div class="alert alert-success mb-3">
                        <div class="d-flex">
                            <div class="me-2">
                                <i class="bi bi-map-fill fs-4 text-success"></i>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <p class="mb-0">On the map, you can see in <span class="text-primary fw-bold">blue</span> all the rivers that escaped sewage in {{year}},
                                    and in <span class="text-warning fw-bold">brown</span> all the rivers that received more than 24 hours of sewage dumps.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="card bg-light mb-4">
                        <div class="card-header bg-success text-white">
                            <h5 class="mb-0">Top of The Poops - Rivers</h5>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-body p-0">
                            <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
                                {{#each riverRankings}}
                                    <li class="list-group-item d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center">
                                        <div>
                                            <span class="badge bg-success rounded-pill me-2">{{this.rank}}</span>
                                            <small class="text-muted me-1">{{this.company.name}} -</small>
                                            <a href="{{this.river.uri}}" class="text-decoration-none">{{this.river.name}}</a>
                                        </div>
                                        <span class="badge bg-danger rounded-pill">{{numberFormat this.duration.hours}} hours</span>
                                    </li>
                                {{/each}}
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <a href="/rivers" class="btn btn-success d-block">
                        <i class="bi bi-water me-1"></i> See All River Rankings
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6 h-100">
            <div class="card border-0  h-100">
                <div class="card-body p-0">
                    <img alt="A map of England and Wales showing major rivers" class="img-fluid rounded" src="/assets/images/top-of-the-poops-rivers-2021.png"/>
                </div>
                <div class="card-footer bg-success text-white py-2">
                    <small><i class="bi bi-info-circle me-1"></i> Map of rivers affected by sewage in {{year}}</small>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>


    <div class="row justify-content-md-center align-items-center my-5 g-4">
        <div class="col-md-5 offset-md-1">
            <div class="card border-0  h-100">
                <div class="card-body p-0">
                    <div id="map-shellfish" class="sewage-map rounded"></div>
                </div>
                <div class="card-footer bg-secondary text-white py-2">
                    <small><i class="bi bi-info-circle me-1"></i> Map of shellfish areas affected by sewage</small>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="card border-0  h-100">
                <div class="card-body p-4">
                    <h2 class="card-title fw-bold text-secondary mb-3">Sewage in the Food Chain?</h2>

                    <div class="alert alert-secondary mb-4">
                        <div class="d-flex">
                            <div class="me-2">
                                <i class="bi bi-exclamation-circle-fill fs-4"></i>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <p class="mb-0">Shellfish are sensitive to the quality of water that surrounds them, and as they filter the water, they can become contaminated
                                with bacteria from the water around them.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="card bg-light mb-4">
                        <div class="card-header bg-secondary text-white">
                            <h5 class="mb-0">Top of The Poops - Shellfish</h5>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-body p-0">
                            <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
                                {{#each shellfishRankings}}
                                    <li class="list-group-item d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center">
                                        <div>
                                            <span class="badge bg-secondary rounded-pill me-2">{{this.rank}}</span>
                                            <small class="text-muted me-1">{{this.company.name}} -</small>
                                            <a href="{{this.shellfish.uri}}" class="text-decoration-none">{{this.shellfish.name}}</a>
                                        </div>
                                        <span class="badge bg-danger rounded-pill">{{numberFormat this.duration.hours}} hours</span>
                                    </li>
                                {{/each}}
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <a href="/shellfisheries" class="btn btn-secondary d-block">
                        <i class="bi bi-list-ol me-1"></i> See All Shellfish Rankings
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

</div>

<div class="container py-5">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col">
            {{#> components/section title="Water Companies" }}
                <div class="row g-4">
                    <div class="col-12 mb-4">
                        <div class="card bg-light border-0 ">
                            <div class="card-body p-4">
                                <h3 class="text-center mb-3">The Companies Responsible</h3>
                                <p class="lead text-center mb-0">These water companies are responsible for managing sewage treatment and preventing pollution in our waterways.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    {{#each companies}}
                        <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-4 col-lg-3">
                            <div class="card h-100 border-0  hover-shadow transition">
                                <div class="card-body">
                                    {{> components/card-company this}}
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    {{/each}}
                </div>
            {{/components/section}}
        </div>
    </div>
</div>


<div class="container py-5 mb-4">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col">
            {{#> components/section title="Top of the Poops in the Media" }}
                <div class="row mb-4">
                    <div class="col-12">
                        <div class="cardbg-light border-0  mb-4">
                            <div class="card-bodyp-4">
                                <h3 class="text-center mb-3">Our Impact in the News</h3>
                                <p class="lead text-center mb-0">Our data and research have been featured in various media outlets, helping to raise awareness about water pollution issues.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="row row-cols-1 row-cols-md-4">
                    {{#each (take appearances n=8)}}
                        {{>components/card-media this}}
                    {{/each}}
                </div>

                <div class="row mt-4 justify-content-center">
                    <div class="col-md-4">
                        <a href="/media" class="btn btn-primary d-block">
                            <i class="bi bi-newspaper me-1"></i> See All {{appearances.length}} Media Appearances
                        </a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            {{/components/section}}
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container py-4">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col">
            <div class="card border-0 ">
                <div class="card-body p-4">
                    <h3 class="card-title text-center mb-4">Our Data Sources</h3>
                    {{> chunks/data-sources }}
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<footer class="bg-dark text-white mt-5 py-4">
    <div class="container">
        {{> chunks/footer }}
        <div class="row mt-3">
            <div class="col-12 text-center">
                <p class="small text-muted mb-0">Â© {{year}} Top of the Poops - Tracking sewage pollution in UK waterways</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</footer>

<script type="module">

    import * as Plot from "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@observablehq/plot@0.6/+esm";

    const formatNumber = (n, m) => n.toLocaleString(undefined, {
        minimumFractionDigits: m ? m : 0,
        maximumFractionDigits: m ? m : 0
    });

    const chart = (data) => {
        let constituencyDiv = document.getElementById("map-constituency");
        const rect = constituencyDiv.getBoundingClientRect()

        constituencyDiv.append(
                Plot.plot({
                    projection: {
                        type: "mercator",
                        domain: {
                            type: "MultiPoint",
                            coordinates: [[-6, 50.0], [1.8, 57.9]],
                        },
                    },
                    height: rect.height,
                    color: {
                        scheme: "oranges",
                    },
                    marks: [
                        Plot.geo(data, {
                            fill: d => d.properties.total_hours,
                            title: d => `${d.properties.constituency}: ${formatNumber(d.properties.total_hours)} hours of sewage`,
                            stroke: "black",
                            strokeOpacity: 0.5,
                        }),
                    ]
                }));
    };

    const r = await fetch("/data/v1/{{year}}/geo/choropleth.json");
    if (r.ok) {
        chart(await r.json())
    }
</script>

<script type="module">
    import * as Plot from "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@observablehq/plot@0.6/+esm";

    const chart = (data, countries) => {
        let beachesDiv = document.getElementById("map-beaches");
        const rect = beachesDiv.getBoundingClientRect()

        return beachesDiv.appendChild(
                Plot.plot(
                        {
                            projection: {
                                type: "mercator",
                                domain: {
                                    type: "MultiPoint",
                                    coordinates: [[-6, 49.9], [1.8, 55.9]],
                                },
                            },
                            height: rect.height,
                            r: {range: [10, 45], domain: [100, 8700]},
                            color: {
                                type: "linear",
                                range: ["steelblue", "#b47846"] // uses d3.interpolateRgb
                            },
                            marks: [
                                Plot.geo(
                                        countries,
                                        {
                                            fill: "rgb(5,118,11)",
                                            fillOpacity: 0.1,
                                            stroke: "#000000",
                                            strokeWidth: 2,
                                            strokeOpacity: 0.2,
                                        }
                                ),
                                Plot.dot(
                                        data,
                                        {
                                            x: "lon",
                                            y: "lat",
                                            r: "total_spill_hours",
                                            fill: "total_spill_hours",
                                            opacity: 0.5,
                                            mixBlendMode: "multiply",
                                            title: d => `${d.bathing} - ${d.total_spill_hours} hours of sewage in {{year}}`,
                                        }
                                )
                            ]
                        }
                )
        );
    }

    const beaches = await fetch("/data/v1/{{year}}/spills-by-beach.json");
    const countries = await fetch("/data/v1/{{year}}/geo/countries.json")
    if (beaches.ok && countries.ok) {
        chart(await beaches.json(), await countries.json())
    }
</script>


<script type="module">
    import * as Plot from "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@observablehq/plot@0.6/+esm";

    const chart = (data, countries) => document.getElementById("map-shellfish").appendChild(
            Plot.plot(
                    {
                        projection: {
                            type: "mercator",
                            domain: {
                                type: "MultiPoint",
                                coordinates: [[-6, 49.9], [1.8, 55.9]],
                            },
                        },
                        height: 800,
                        r: {range: [10, 45], domain: [100, 8700]},
                        color: {
                            type: "linear",
                            range: ["#8e2353", "#b47846"] // uses d3.interpolateRgb
                        },
                        marks: [
                            Plot.geo(
                                    countries,
                                    {
                                        fill: "rgb(77,5,118)",
                                        fillOpacity: 0.1,
                                        stroke: "#000000",
                                        strokeWidth: 2,
                                        strokeOpacity: 0.2,
                                    }
                            ),
                            Plot.dot(
                                    data,
                                    {
                                        x: "lon",
                                        y: "lat",
                                        r: "total_spill_hours",
                                        fill: "total_spill_hours",
                                        opacity: 0.5,
                                        mixBlendMode: "multiply",
                                        title: d => `${d.shellfishery} - ${d.total_spill_hours} hours of sewage in {{year}}`,
                                    }
                            )
                        ]
                    }
            )
    )

    const shellfish = await fetch("/data/v1/{{year}}/spills-by-shellfish.json");
    const countries = await fetch("/data/v1/{{year}}/geo/countries.json")
    if (shellfish.ok && countries.ok) {
        chart(await shellfish.json(), await countries.json())
    }
</script>


</body>
</html>
